Kandenko Co. (1942) , an engineering
company partly owned by  Tokyo Electric Power Co. (9501) , will build two
solar power stations in southwestern Japan.  The plants, to be built in Fukuoka prefecture, will have a
combined capacity of about 19 megawatts, the company said in a
statement today.  Construction of the plants will cost about 6.7 billion yen
($71 million) and theyâ€™ll start running by June 2016, according
to the statement. Tepco has a 46 percent stake in the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
